memberdef.argsstring: (uint16_t size=0, const image_type format=i_png, bool prefer_animated=true) const
memberdef.name: get_banner_url

briefdescription.para: Get the banner url of the guild if it have one, otherwise returns an empty string.

parameterdescription.para: The size of the banner in pixels. It can be any power of two between 16 and 4096, otherwise the default sized banner is returned.

The format to use for the avatar. It can be one of i_webp, i_jpg, i_png or i_gif. Passing i_gif might result in an invalid url for non-animated images. Consider using the prefer_animated parameter instead.
Whether you prefer gif format. If true, it'll return gif format whenever the image is available as animated.

simplesect.para: std::string banner url or an empty string, if required attributes are missing or an invalid format was passed

simplesect.para: std::string discovery splash url or an empty string, if required attributes are missing or an invalid format was passed
